article.headline: Howard 41, Cheyney 14
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Brian Johnson threw two touchdown passes and ran for another as Howard beat Cheyney 41-14 on Saturday. Johnson wasted no time, running for a 28-yard touchdown on Howard's first possession and throwing for two other scores in the first half. He completed 12 of 19 passes for 184 yards in the game, with one interception. Howard's Terry Perry added two rushing touchdowns of his own, gaining 79 yards on 18 carries. Howard (2-3) wore down Division II Cheyney (1-5), as the Bison gained 439 yards of offense compared to the Wolves' 214 yards. But it wasn't until Perry gave Howard a 34-14 lead on a 1-yard touchdown early in the fourth quarter that the Bison appeared completely in control. Cheyney hung around through much of the first three quarters, mostly due to its passing game. Derrick Murry completed 14 of 37 passes for 138 yards with two touchdowns and an interception for the Wolves. On one Cheyney second-quarter drive, Howard's Randell Means was twice flagged in the end zone for pass interference on fourth-down-and-goal plays. However, the Bison preserved their 21-7 lead when Cheyney lost a fumbled snap on its third first-and-goal of the 16-play drive.
